From a496bbfbee7a26f0a9a9c0d9f1ab70509c5b1f2e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jake Teton-Landis <just.1.jake@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 03:19:35 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 13/25] Existence proofs: per-root commit facts under
 multi-root schedules
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Spec §4.4 tests 15-17 and 25 — the fact cluster the spec names as having no
current-generation React existence proof, scheduled before any bindings
(§8). All four PROVEN against current React through the channel:

- 15: a transition spanning two createRoots is reported per root, with that
  root's commit generation, when THAT root commits — while the token stays
  live until the last root finishes; retirement follows the final report.
- 16: both roots committing in one flush report separately (right
  container, exactly once per root); retirement after the LAST report;
  generation counters advance per root, independently.
- 17: a root whose share of the batch is pruned (pending update deleted
  with its subtree) NEVER reports the batch — prune ≠ commit — and the
  prune happens at the deleting commit itself, where the token still
  retires exactly once with committed=true because the other root did
  commit it.
- 25: write-set closure — at every commit of every root, the committing
  pass's included batches equal the commit's reported delta plus the live
  batches already in the root's table (lock-ins): a pending-unrendered
  batch never leaks in, a committed one is never dropped. Checked as an
  invariant over the whole event log.
